THE SOLUTION 

In the days following, LarvaLabs created a new Smart Contract with duplicate CryptoPunks which were airdropped to claimants of the original token.

The ‚ÄòV1s‚Äô were soon forgotten and the CryptoPunks story continued on with the ‚ÄòV2‚Äô tokens instead.

The ‚Äòbuyer‚Äô was left with a CryptoPunk and their funds returned, the seller was left with neither.

~80 Punks were affected by this error and LarvaLabs requested users cease trading until they could find a solution.

Did you know.. this is the first Tweet by LarvaLabs in 2017 alerting the community about the bug in the smart contract.üêõ

CryptoPunks existed before the term or even concept of ‚ÄúNFTs‚Äù did. 

It was the first profile picture collectible on Ethereum and a first of its kind within crypto. 

Everything that exists today within NFTs has at least one direct line of influence to this humble experiment.

The reason for this is because the only available token format in 2017 was ERC-20.  

You can also unwrap at will.

In order to trade on marketplaces such as @LooksRareNFT or @opensea NFTs require the standard ERC-721.

Step 5: Morale

If you use Discord, don't click on any link, even if it's sent by your most trusted friend, ask them kindly to send it again via Twitter, telegram or any other medium of communication you use with them.

If you don't know them, just ignore any link coming your way

Step 4: The Transfer

Unfortunately they managed to steal ETH, V1 Punks and other assets, and our community is working together, hard, to trace everything.

The trail ends to a bunch of tornado txs. https://t.co/xQtSFulePs https://t.co/59XGiMwCoC
They even renamed the attacker Rvph‚Äôs discord name to @irishnftgal to continue posing from what appeared to be official moderator accounts. https://t.co/oNI6ZnqP1b

"YourBoyXav" and "Daniel" gave themselves admin permissions. They created a webhook in the announcements channel and made it so everything written there would be deleted, aside from the fake link.üëá https://t.co/NnQkurikwb

Step 3: The Proxy

They now have access to an admin account, but they didn't attack right away, they planned it out properly, waited for some hype and in the meantime accessed the server using Velinova's account to give themselves permissions.üëá https://t.co/bwzmhFjGfA

- A JS code which grabs your token from the local storage
- A webhook connected to the "attacker", which is how the token is sent to them.

That's it. It's just a simple exploit mixed with social engineering.

And looked like this (don't worry is an image, you are safe) https://t.co/QjNCeM5dyk

Step 2: The Link

This type of attack is called "bookmarklet".

Discord has this EXTREMELY unsafe bad practice of storing user tokens in the local storage ü§¶

The link has two elements üëá

Step 1: Social Engineering

An admin and mod on several servers, incl. ours - @ChristinaMiyar was tricked into clicking a malicious link. This attack took over two weeks. She was hired for a very realistic job as a dev. They gained her trust.

The attacker waited for the perfect timing. They started to plan while we were hosting our weekly Twitter Spaces. The theme this week was conveniently ‚ÄúCyber Security‚Äù.

While the V1s still exist in their original form, so does the existing bug in the V1 contract, so NEVER put an unwrapped V1 on sale as you will most likely loose it. 

/7

This recovery of the original Punks smart contract is a community led and rapidly growing phenomenon consisting of original Punk claimants, NFT historians, digital archeologists and extremely talented developers.
 
/6

Wrapping is like putting the NFT into a transparent box allowing it to be transported and shipped when the original version did not have these functions. You can also unwrap your NFT. 

Learn how to unwrap/wrap your punk in our discord channel: https://t.co/xBMoTRBeaA

/5

Recognisable by it‚Äôs lavender background colour.

But what does it mean to wrap an NFT?
When you wrap, you deposit the NFT into another smart contract. Allowing it to be traded on secondary markets such as opensea and fixes any bugs on the original NFT contract.

/4

Not long after the bug was found a newer version of the Punks contract (V2) was released and Punks were airdropped to the original claimers. 

To fix this bug, Cryptopunks v1 wrapper was born, making it safe to trade on secondary marketplaces.

/3

In the original Cryptopunks smart contract, there was a code error that caused Ethereum to be allocated to the buyer instead of the seller when a purchase was made. In other words, a buyer was immediately refunded for their purchase and was able to keep the Punk.  

/2

Launched in June 2017 by Larva Labs, Cryptopunks were originally free for anyone with an Ethereum wallet to claim (+ gas). 

/1

The history of Cryptopunks and why you need to understand the use-cases of our Cryptopunks v1 wrapper.
